{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "10", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "01", "M": "46", "S": "35"}}, "news": [{"title": "Merger of banks does not shield tenant from eviction under Delhi Rent Control Act: SC", "para": "The Supreme Court ruled bank mergers do not exempt tenants from eviction without landlord consent.  Punjab National Bank must vacate premises by January 2027 after a long legal battle.  The court found amalgamation did not override the Delhi Rent Control Act's provisions.  This decision ends a dispute dating back to 1987.  The ruling clarifies tenant responsibilities in bank mergers.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/supreme-court-rules-bank-merger-does-not-prevent-tenant-eviction-under-delhi-rent-control-act/132288970?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-274864/132288970.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Gurugram realty fraud: Delhi court says ED summons to foreign-based son of accused invalid", "para": "A Delhi court ruled ED summons invalid for a foreign national residing abroad.  The agency must follow legal procedures for serving overseas individuals.  This decision impacts the Enforcement Directorate's investigation into real estate fraud allegations.  Amit Katyal, the accused, sought to restrain the ED from valid service on his son.  The court emphasized due process for individuals living outside India.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/delhi-court-invalidates-ed-summons-to-amit-katyals-son-in-realty-fraud-case/132288796?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-241018/132288796.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Amaravati phase-I work on track, to be completed by next year: Andhra Pradesh minister", "para": "Minister P Narayana co